title: North Carolina Center for Geographic Information and Analysis (NCCGIA), Districts - NC Senate, North Carolina, 2003
name: North Carolina Center for Geographic Information and Analysis (NCCGIA), Districts - NC Senate, North Carolina, 2003
description:
The NC Center for Geographic Information and Analysis acquired the voting districts shapefiles for the state of North Carolina from the General Assembly/Information Systems Division. These data represent the boundaries of 2003 Senate Districts in North Carolina, ratified Nov. 25, 2003. Each district is labeled with unique district identification number. The shapefiles were processed into ARC/INFO coverages and projected from Decimal Degrees to Stateplane NAD83 meters projection.

These data were created to display the boundaries of voting districts, and to enable users to display voting districts with other geographic features.
